article.headline: Smith scores 7 of her 15 in final 3 minutes
article.linkText: Smith's late surge propels Lynx over Stars
article.story:
MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Late in a close game, the Minnesota Lynx did
something unsurprising: They got the ball to Katie Smith.

Smith scored 13 of her 15 points in the second half, and the
Lynx pulled away for a 55-47 victory over the San Antonio Silver
Stars on Thursday night.

"Katie can always hit big shots, and we have confidence in her
to do that," Lynx coach Suzie McConnell Serio said. "This team
will feed off Katie."

The game was tied 45-45 with 3:15 to play, then Minnesota closed
the game with a 10-2 run. Reserve Michele Van Gorp scored 13 points
for the Lynx (3-3).

LaToya Thomas had 12 points for the Silver Stars (3-3), who
scored 14 points off 23 Minnesota turnovers, but lost their second
straight game.

"We felt pretty confident throughout," Thomas said. "With two
minutes left we still felt like we had a good chance to win the
game, but they matched our intensity right at the end."

Adrienne Goodson added 11 points for San Antonio, which took a
41-40 lead on Goodson's 3-pointer with 5:20 to play.

"We lost it, won it, and lost it again all in that five-minute
stretch," San Antonio coach Dee Brown said. "It's tough to come
back from that, especially after playing well for 35 minutes and
putting ourselves in a position to win."

Smith hit a 3-pointer and made four free throws in the final
three minutes for the Lynx, who have won five of six games against
San Antonio since the Silver Stars moved there before the 2003
season.

"That kind of gave us a little breathing room," Smith said of
the 3-pointer. "I felt good shooting it, and I'm just glad it went
down."

Minnesota threatened to pull away in the first half, taking a
seven-point lead on the strength of eight points from Van Gorp. But
15 first-half turnovers by the Lynx allowed San Antonio to forge a
28-28 halftime tie.

"U-G-L-Y. That was ugly," McConnell Serio said of her team's
numerous turnovers. "We dodged a big bullet with them only
capitalizing for 14 points."
